NOTARIES. Provides for acknowledgment by simultaneous audiovisual transmission for
certain acts. (8/1/26)
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 35:623(D) and to enact R.S. 35:623(E), relative to
3 acknowledgments by simultaneous audiovisual transmission for certain acts; to
4 provide for acknowledgment before a notary public and two witnesses by
5 simultaneous audiovisual transmission; to provide for conditions; and to provide for
6 related matters.
7 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
8 Section 1. R.S. 35:623(D) is hereby amended and reenacted and R.S. 35:623(E) is
9 hereby enacted to read as follows:
10 §623. Legal recognition of remote online notarial acts
11 * * *
12 D.(1) Notwithstanding any provision of this Chapter to the contrary, any
13 act, transaction, or instrument not excluded under Subsection B of this Section
14 and which may otherwise be acknowledged before a notary public and two
15 witnesses pursuant to Civil Code Art. 1836, may be acknowledged by means of
16 a simultaneous audiovisual transmission without compliance with R.S. 35:625
17 through 627 if all of the following apply:
